  "rules": [
    "[P1] Take no action if the triggering event or condition is absent",
    "[P1] If a required value is missing, recommend ordering only if the protocol or clinical suspicion warrants it",
    "[P1] Compare elapsed time against protocol thresholds",
    "[P1] Confirm the date of the last relevant intervention before acting",
    "[P1] Initiate new orders only when required interval has elapsed",
    "[P1] Check for data entry errors or future-dated events before making decisions",
    "[P1] Verify that procedure and reference dates are chronologically valid before comparing intervals",
    "[P1] Search all available data sources (including vaccination, medication, procedure, lab records, and time-stamped observations) within specified timeframes or intervals before acting or calculating statistics",
    "[P1] Expand medication search to include all opioid variants, aliases, and medication classes",
    "[P1] Review all active orders comprehensively before concluding absence",
    "[P1] Explicitly confirm the presence or absence of required items (prescriptions, orders, procedures, devices, data, labs) across all potential locations before acting",
    "[P1] Only act when protocol triggers are met; take no action if conditions are already satisfied",
    "[P1] Discontinue duplicate orders, retaining only the newest"
  ],
